WEBVTT

﻿1
00:00:06.000 --> 00:00:12.074
Tired of searching for subtitles?
Ray generates them instantly: getray.app

2
00:00:25.887 --> 00:00:27.924
♪♪

3
00:00:42.007 --> 00:00:44.044
<i>[crowd clamoring]</i>

4
00:00:46.356 --> 00:00:50.119
-[boot thumping]
-CROWD: One! Two! Three!

5
00:00:50.257 --> 00:00:51.879
[laughs menacingly]

6
00:00:52.017 --> 00:00:53.536
Yeah!

7
00:00:53.674 --> 00:00:55.469
[yells]

8
00:00:55.607 --> 00:00:57.402
[yells. grunts]

9
00:00:57.540 --> 00:00:59.438
[cheering]

10
00:00:59.576 --> 00:01:01.061
Come on! Yeah!

11
00:01:03.649 --> 00:01:04.649
Come on!

12
00:01:04.685 --> 00:01:06.411
[yells]

13
00:01:06.549 --> 00:01:09.069
-[laughs]
-[crowd shouting]

14
00:01:13.487 --> 00:01:15.005
Let's do this! Come on!

15
00:01:15.144 --> 00:01:16.697
Come on!

16
00:01:16.835 --> 00:01:19.251
[yells. grunts]

17
00:01:20.459 --> 00:01:22.737
Come on! Come on!

18
00:01:22.875 --> 00:01:24.291
[chair clatters]

19
00:01:24.429 --> 00:01:26.086
[grunts] Come on.

20
00:01:26.224 --> 00:01:27.501
Let's do this. Come on.

21
00:01:27.639 --> 00:01:29.123
[crowd shouting]

22
00:01:29.261 --> 00:01:31.470
[wrestlers grunting]

23
00:01:36.303 --> 00:01:39.444
MAN: Let the backpack slip off
next time everyone stands.

24
00:01:45.795 --> 00:01:47.624
[cheering]

25
00:01:53.768 --> 00:01:54.873
Where's Jane?

26
00:01:55.011 --> 00:01:56.771
Daniel Kellner.

27
00:01:56.909 --> 00:01:59.049
Do you want to see her again
or not?

28
00:02:03.088 --> 00:02:05.815
[crowd cheering]

29
00:02:10.130 --> 00:02:11.545
Relax.

30
00:02:11.683 --> 00:02:13.029
Enjoy the match.

31
00:02:13.167 --> 00:02:15.307
Just got to make sure
it's all there.

32
00:02:15.445 --> 00:02:17.447
[crowd cheering]

33
00:02:19.691 --> 00:02:23.384
MAN 2:7.23.48.83

34
00:02:23.522 --> 00:02:28.044
through 3.14.84A.

35
00:02:28.182 --> 00:02:29.839
11.17.55...

36
00:02:29.977 --> 00:02:34.361
I make a total of 107
IronClad drives. 128 gig each.

37
00:02:34.499 --> 00:02:37.502
-You want me to do a recount?
-Uh. when we finish. yes.

38
00:02:37.640 --> 00:02:39.918
Printed documents
approximately 200 pages.

39
00:02:40.056 --> 00:02:41.575
What's the date range?

40
00:02:41.713 --> 00:02:43.542
Uh. we can catalog that
when we get back.

41
00:02:43.680 --> 00:02:46.235
But I'm seeing
as far back as 1947

42
00:02:46.373 --> 00:02:48.409
and as recent as last year.

43
00:02:49.824 --> 00:02:51.723
[door creaks open]

44
00:02:51.861 --> 00:02:53.863
[lively crowd chatter
in distance]

45
00:02:59.040 --> 00:03:01.077
♪♪

46
00:03:14.746 --> 00:03:16.748
[breathing heavily]

47
00:03:28.518 --> 00:03:30.589
Well. this is all
rather disappointing.

48
00:03:33.282 --> 00:03:34.731
Where's Jane?

49
00:03:38.528 --> 00:03:40.530
[trembling breaths]

50
00:03:45.397 --> 00:03:47.123
-Are you okay?
-Yeah.

51
00:03:48.642 --> 00:03:50.885
-DANIEL: Careful.
-[snips zip tie]

52
00:03:53.060 --> 00:03:54.889
-[Jane whimpering]
-Hey.

53
00:04:01.793 --> 00:04:03.588
Who turned you?

54
00:04:03.726 --> 00:04:07.764
Give me the names. all of them.
and you two can call a cab.

55
00:04:07.902 --> 00:04:09.766
It's here.

56
00:04:29.303 --> 00:04:30.960
[backpack drops to ground]

57
00:04:32.893 --> 00:04:34.274
Where is it?

58
00:04:39.486 --> 00:04:41.049
-Put your weapon on the ground!
-[others shouting]

59
00:04:41.073 --> 00:04:44.456
Do not fire! Do not fire.

60
00:04:44.594 --> 00:04:47.252
If you fire.
it could activate the device.

61
00:04:49.150 --> 00:04:51.152
Loosen your grip. Daniel.

62
00:04:52.188 --> 00:04:54.294
If you squeeze. it activates.
Soften your grip.

63
00:04:55.743 --> 00:04:57.642
Put it down.
You don't know how to use it.

64
00:04:57.780 --> 00:04:59.851
-I know how you used it.
-And it almost killed me.

65
00:04:59.989 --> 00:05:03.372
Now. place the device
on the ground.

66
00:05:03.510 --> 00:05:05.477
I should do to you
what you did to them.

67
00:05:05.615 --> 00:05:07.479
Stand down. Serena.

68
00:05:07.617 --> 00:05:10.171
[breathing heavily]

69
00:05:11.276 --> 00:05:14.314
Do not exert any pressure on it.

70
00:05:14.452 --> 00:05:16.868
Just loosen your grip.

71
00:05:17.006 --> 00:05:18.456
Loosen your grip. That's it.

72
00:05:18.594 --> 00:05:20.009
Just open your hand.

73
00:05:21.148 --> 00:05:22.183
That's it.

74
00:05:22.322 --> 00:05:23.978
Okay. Okay.

75
00:05:25.842 --> 00:05:28.017
Sweep everything into
the backpack and get in the car.

76
00:05:28.155 --> 00:05:29.605
Please. Jane.

77
00:05:32.193 --> 00:05:33.643
Get out.

78
00:05:39.373 --> 00:05:41.341
You're not running
some malware op.

79
00:05:41.479 --> 00:05:43.998
You can't hide behind a screen
in your SCIF.

80
00:05:44.136 --> 00:05:45.586
The world is on the brink.

81
00:05:45.724 --> 00:05:47.761
Do you actually believe
that dumping inventory

82
00:05:47.899 --> 00:05:50.384
will be anything more
than a dangerous distraction?

83
00:05:51.730 --> 00:05:53.353
I watched the interrogations.

84
00:05:54.457 --> 00:05:55.907
History doesn't have
a reset key.

85
00:05:56.045 --> 00:05:57.702
If you do this.
there's no undoing it.

86
00:05:59.876 --> 00:06:01.706
That's the plan.

87
00:06:02.603 --> 00:06:03.604
[engine starts]

88
00:06:05.813 --> 00:06:07.953
[tires squealing]

89
00:06:15.375 --> 00:06:17.031
Boyd.

90
00:06:21.139 --> 00:06:23.072
He sits at a desk.

91
00:06:24.314 --> 00:06:26.144
How did he beat you?

92
00:06:35.049 --> 00:06:36.637
They said you committed treason?

93
00:06:36.775 --> 00:06:38.339
It's not treason.
They're not the government.

94
00:06:38.363 --> 00:06:39.778
and they lie for a living.

95
00:06:39.916 --> 00:06:41.608
What is going on. Daniel?

96
00:06:41.746 --> 00:06:43.023
Their cars have trackers.

97
00:06:43.161 --> 00:06:44.438
We got to get rid of this.

98
00:06:44.576 --> 00:06:45.853
Please just take me home.

99
00:06:45.991 --> 00:06:47.959
They'd be waiting
at your apartment.

100
00:06:48.097 --> 00:06:50.168
Hey. hand me
the clear plastic bag.

101
00:06:53.620 --> 00:06:55.622
Okay. Steer for a second.

102
00:06:57.209 --> 00:06:59.557
Okay. Okay.

103
00:07:02.491 --> 00:07:03.802
[dialing phone]

104
00:07:03.940 --> 00:07:05.977
-Okay. okay.
-[line ringing]

105
00:07:06.115 --> 00:07:07.634
Hugo. I'm clear.

106
00:07:07.772 --> 00:07:10.291
HUGO [over phone]:
Daniel. I'm so proud of you.

107
00:07:10.430 --> 00:07:12.466
They kidnapped Jane
to get to me.

108
00:07:12.604 --> 00:07:14.192
She's with me now.

109
00:07:14.330 --> 00:07:15.918
HUGO: Is she all right?

110
00:07:16.056 --> 00:07:17.540
Not really. Hugo.

111
00:07:17.678 --> 00:07:18.990
Where do I do the drop?

112
00:07:19.128 --> 00:07:20.612
-No drop yet.
-[power tools buzzing]

113
00:07:20.750 --> 00:07:22.614
-Get secure. and then...
-DANIEL: No. no. no.

114
00:07:22.752 --> 00:07:24.616
Send the guy for the bag now.

115
00:07:24.754 --> 00:07:26.446
Somebody needs to run
with this thing.

116
00:07:26.584 --> 00:07:27.861
That's you.

117
00:07:27.999 --> 00:07:29.345
You've got the ball.

118
00:07:30.450 --> 00:07:32.244
I don't want the ball.

119
00:07:32.382 --> 00:07:35.040
No. the plan was I get it out
of the facility. and I-I did.

120
00:07:35.178 --> 00:07:36.698
HUGO: I decided
you were best qualified

121
00:07:36.766 --> 00:07:38.043
to keep the material safe.

122
00:07:38.181 --> 00:07:40.149
Are you out of your mind?

123
00:07:40.287 --> 00:07:42.669
No. I'm not a field guy. Hugo.

124
00:07:42.807 --> 00:07:44.981
I-I did the tech work.
That's all I can do.

125
00:07:45.119 --> 00:07:46.120
You just stay with me.

126
00:07:46.258 --> 00:07:47.639
We're on plan.

127
00:07:47.777 --> 00:07:50.193
Waiting now for someone else
to be activated.

128
00:07:50.331 --> 00:07:52.575
When they are.
we'll know what comes next.

129
00:07:52.713 --> 00:07:55.267
Leave Jane somewhere safe
and get secure for the night.

130
00:07:55.405 --> 00:07:57.994
Oh. no.
I-I'm not leaving her alone.

131
00:07:58.132 --> 00:08:00.687
-She'll be safer without you.
-But she wasn't.

132
00:08:00.825 --> 00:08:03.690
I'm gonna need you to drop
a marker when you get secure.

133
00:08:03.828 --> 00:08:06.002
Our friend Santiago
will find you in the morning.

134
00:08:06.140 --> 00:08:09.350
I should just dump everything
online right now.

135
00:08:11.145 --> 00:08:14.286
You cannot. under any
circumstances. do that.

136
00:08:15.909 --> 00:08:17.186
For now. we wait.

137
00:08:17.324 --> 00:08:19.119
Stay alert. Find shelter.

138
00:08:19.257 --> 00:08:21.328
Santiago will put us together
in the morning.

139
00:08:22.329 --> 00:08:23.572
Destroy your phone.

140
00:08:23.710 --> 00:08:25.021
[sighs]

141
00:08:25.159 --> 00:08:26.575
[siren wailing in distance]

142
00:08:26.713 --> 00:08:28.059
Danny.

143
00:08:28.197 --> 00:08:30.406
Satellite burner phones.

144
00:08:30.544 --> 00:08:31.994
They got their own
encrypted network.

145
00:08:32.132 --> 00:08:33.858
We only use them once.

146
00:08:36.516 --> 00:08:38.552
What exactly do you do
for a living?

147
00:08:40.002 --> 00:08:41.486
We got to get secure
for the night.

148
00:08:41.624 --> 00:08:43.453
No apartments. no motels.

149
00:08:43.592 --> 00:08:46.318
Has to be somewhere I've never
been before in my life.

150
00:08:47.665 --> 00:08:49.943
I know a place close to here.

151
00:09:01.817 --> 00:09:03.059
<i>[elevator bell chimes]</i>

152
00:09:03.197 --> 00:09:05.959
Musgrave at DoD wants
a briefing.

153
00:09:06.097 --> 00:09:08.168
SCANLON:
Get Wakefield down here now.

154
00:09:08.306 --> 00:09:10.032
Tell Musgrave
it was a minor breach.

155
00:09:10.170 --> 00:09:11.585
Recovery is in process.

156
00:09:11.723 --> 00:09:13.449
Sir. he will not want
to hear it from me.

157
00:09:13.587 --> 00:09:15.589
If I pick up the phone.
it means I'm concerned.

158
00:09:15.727 --> 00:09:17.602
If they even get a whiff
of that. we'll have the entire

159
00:09:17.626 --> 00:09:19.904
military and intelligence
apparatus up here in an hour.

160
00:09:20.042 --> 00:09:21.319
Handle him.

161
00:09:21.457 --> 00:09:23.017
Anything relevant to this
on news feeds?

162
00:09:23.079 --> 00:09:24.287
Not yet.

163
00:09:24.425 --> 00:09:26.013
Socials or secure private?

164
00:09:26.151 --> 00:09:27.705
All quiet.

165
00:09:31.122 --> 00:09:32.951
12 no-shows here today.

166
00:09:36.506 --> 00:09:38.336
All with empty desks.

167
00:09:38.474 --> 00:09:40.752
All clearance above G5.

168
00:09:40.890 --> 00:09:42.892
[busy chatter]

169
00:09:49.450 --> 00:09:52.108
All right. so we're dealing
with an operation

170
00:09:52.246 --> 00:09:55.318
carefully coordinated
and executed.

171
00:09:56.699 --> 00:09:59.322
Why? With what goal?

172
00:09:59.460 --> 00:10:00.945
If they wanted the archive out.

173
00:10:01.083 --> 00:10:02.543
Kellner would have
already released it.

174
00:10:02.567 --> 00:10:03.948
but he hasn't. which means

175
00:10:04.086 --> 00:10:05.743
somebody's maintaining
decision space.

176
00:10:05.881 --> 00:10:09.539
But for how long. we don't know.
so think quickly.

177
00:10:09.678 --> 00:10:11.162
Daniel Kellner has a doctorate

178
00:10:11.300 --> 00:10:12.991
in theoretical
and applied cybersecurity.

179
00:10:13.129 --> 00:10:14.889
and he's spent the better part
of eight years

180
00:10:14.959 --> 00:10:16.477
safeguarding high-side data.

181
00:10:16.616 --> 00:10:18.376
so what does that
tell us about him?

182
00:10:18.514 --> 00:10:19.688
Ideas.

183
00:10:19.826 --> 00:10:20.906
-Come on.
-He built the firewalls.

184
00:10:20.930 --> 00:10:22.552
He knows how to breach them.

185
00:10:22.691 --> 00:10:24.254
They're already breached.
We got to play past that.

186
00:10:24.278 --> 00:10:25.670
AGENT: We got to maintain
standard skip tracing.

187
00:10:25.694 --> 00:10:27.016
AGENT 2:
Well. I can access SYNTRAK.

188
00:10:27.040 --> 00:10:28.520
SERENA:
What's the next thing he does?

189
00:10:28.593 --> 00:10:30.802
BOYD: Sir.

190
00:10:30.940 --> 00:10:33.702
Hugo Wakefield didn't show up
for work this morning.

191
00:10:35.635 --> 00:10:38.292
[sighs]
His desk was cleaned out.

192
00:10:38.430 --> 00:10:40.018
Hugo?

193
00:10:43.194 --> 00:10:46.300
Second device is missing
from deep storage.

194
00:10:46.438 --> 00:10:48.164
Where's the third?

195
00:10:48.302 --> 00:10:50.028
Locked down in the cold room.

196
00:10:54.136 --> 00:10:56.138
♪♪

197
00:11:16.158 --> 00:11:18.160
♪♪

198
00:11:25.408 --> 00:11:26.616
[vehicle door closes]

199
00:11:30.828 --> 00:11:33.554
DANIEL: How do you know
they'll answer it?

200
00:11:33.693 --> 00:11:35.384
'Cause that's what we do.

201
00:11:36.419 --> 00:11:38.145
How do you know this place?

202
00:11:42.736 --> 00:11:44.186
Jane.

203
00:11:45.497 --> 00:11:48.259
[sobbing]: Oh... oh. my dear.

204
00:11:52.470 --> 00:11:54.921
The monsignor has finally
surrendered his sneakers.

205
00:11:55.059 --> 00:11:56.405
-Oh.
-[chuckling]

206
00:11:56.543 --> 00:11:57.993
Oh. I couldn't bear
his other shoes.

207
00:11:58.131 --> 00:12:00.305
I know. They always
squeaked so horribly.

208
00:12:00.443 --> 00:12:01.513
[both laughing]

209
00:12:01.651 --> 00:12:04.137
[imitating squeaking footsteps]

210
00:12:04.275 --> 00:12:07.727
Oh. we have missed you
very much. my dear.

211
00:12:07.865 --> 00:12:09.590
Oh. come on.

212
00:12:09.729 --> 00:12:11.568
All I ever did was drive you
and the other sisters crazy.

213
00:12:11.592 --> 00:12:15.148
Mm. well. you do ask
a lot of questions.

214
00:12:15.286 --> 00:12:17.219
Did Teresa ever get through
her postulancy?

215
00:12:17.357 --> 00:12:18.634
She sailed through.

216
00:12:18.772 --> 00:12:20.774
Once she stopped
sneaking out at night.

217
00:12:20.912 --> 00:12:22.362
JANE: No.

218
00:12:22.500 --> 00:12:23.580
SISTER MAURA:
The monsignor has her teaching

219
00:12:23.604 --> 00:12:25.434
third grade at St. Anthony's.

220
00:12:25.572 --> 00:12:27.747
JANE: Oh. she'll be
fantastic with kids.

221
00:12:27.885 --> 00:12:30.094
BOTH: Saint Benedicta.

222
00:12:32.717 --> 00:12:35.651
Hold this against your eye.

223
00:12:43.245 --> 00:12:45.419
I'm not going to ask you
any questions.

224
00:12:45.557 --> 00:12:46.973
It's not my business.

225
00:12:47.111 --> 00:12:49.113
But Jane is.

226
00:12:50.148 --> 00:12:53.807
Whatever you have done. you must
hold yourself accountable.

227
00:12:53.945 --> 00:12:57.017
But leave Jane out of it.

228
00:12:57.155 --> 00:12:59.433
She can stay with us.

229
00:13:04.300 --> 00:13:05.923
[chuckling]: You were a nun?

230
00:13:07.372 --> 00:13:09.892
We've had sex.
What do you think?

231
00:13:10.030 --> 00:13:13.482
I think everything you told me
about yourself isn't true.

232
00:13:14.828 --> 00:13:16.865
You have an enormous
amount of nerve.

233
00:13:17.003 --> 00:13:19.108
Yeah. I kept things to myself

234
00:13:19.246 --> 00:13:21.801
because I had to sign away
my life. but your thing...

235
00:13:21.939 --> 00:13:24.631
[chuckles]
You were an actual nun?

236
00:13:24.769 --> 00:13:26.529
A novitiate.

237
00:13:26.667 --> 00:13:27.787
Why didn't you say anything?

238
00:13:27.910 --> 00:13:29.291
I omitted a portion of my story.

239
00:13:29.429 --> 00:13:30.499
People judge you.

240
00:13:33.467 --> 00:13:35.366
When was all this?

241
00:13:36.401 --> 00:13:38.024
Three years ago.

242
00:13:38.162 --> 00:13:41.061
And I'm not answering
any more questions until you do.

243
00:13:42.787 --> 00:13:44.340
What did you steal?

244
00:13:46.826 --> 00:13:49.414
I stole the data
they paid me to protect.

245
00:13:49.552 --> 00:13:51.347
Why would you do that?

246
00:13:52.659 --> 00:13:54.419
'Cause people have a right
to know the truth.

247
00:13:55.662 --> 00:13:58.803
And what is it.
this truth you stole?

248
00:14:01.012 --> 00:14:02.807
So...

249
00:14:02.945 --> 00:14:06.846
you wanted to be a nun.
but what. you lost your faith?

250
00:14:07.881 --> 00:14:09.572
I lost my calling.

251
00:14:09.710 --> 00:14:12.437
How long have you worked
for these people?

252
00:14:12.575 --> 00:14:14.301
Since. um...

253
00:14:18.236 --> 00:14:20.480
Since I got out...

254
00:14:20.618 --> 00:14:22.827
of federal prison
eight years ago.

255
00:14:26.762 --> 00:14:31.249
I did 19 months in Petersburg
for cybercrimes.

256
00:14:31.387 --> 00:14:33.631
WARDEX recruited me
straight out of the parking lot

257
00:14:33.769 --> 00:14:35.667
the day I was released.

258
00:14:35.805 --> 00:14:38.153
-Even with your record?
-Because of my record.

259
00:14:39.257 --> 00:14:40.569
I keep secrets for a living.

260
00:14:40.707 --> 00:14:43.986
I-I didn't mean
to keep them from you.

261
00:14:44.124 --> 00:14:47.610
Three months ago. I didn't know
half of what I know now.

262
00:14:49.267 --> 00:14:50.717
Jane...

263
00:14:52.615 --> 00:14:54.410
I'm doing the right thing.

264
